OL,3,CNurses face 'abhorrent' levels of
OL,4,Cviolence as A&E attacks double in five
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,FNurses are facing "abhorrent" levels
OL,8,Fof violence as attacks in A&E wards
OL,9,Fhave almost doubled in the last five
OL,10,Fyears, new figures reveal.
OL,12,FStaff have been punched, spat at and
OL,13,Feven had a gun pointed at one of them
OL,14,Fin A&E departments.
OL,16,FLong waits in A&E are also leading to
OL,17,Fanger among patients who are not prone
OL,18,Fto violence, the Royal College of
OL,19,FNursing (RCN) said as it called for
OL,20,Fmore to be done to protect NHS staff.
